If your GitHub Pages website is only showing the word “Smartvolt”, that means the HTML file is very simple or not properly set up.

Let’s fix this from the start.

✅ Step-by-step to get your SmartVolt website working

1. Create a new basic HTML file

Here’s a simple website for SmartVolt:

html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>SmartVolt</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      text-align: center;
      background: #f0f0f0;
      padding: 50px;
    }
    h1 {
      color: #0077cc;
    }
    p {
      font-size: 18px;
      color: #333;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>SmartVolt</h1>
  <p>Smart energy solutions: solar panel installation, socket & lighting services, and more.</p>
</body>
</html>

2. Upload to GitHub

  • Go to your repo (e.g., smartvolt)

  • Create a file called: index.html

  • Paste the above code

  • Commit to the main branch

3. Enable GitHub Pages

  • Go to Settings > Pages

  • Under Branch, select main and / (root)

  • Click Save

  • GitHub will give you a website URL like:

    arduino
    https://your-username.github.io/smartvolt/

4. View your site

After 1–2 minutes, visit the link. You should now see the SmartVolt name plus a description.
